We gave this place 3 solid tries before deciding not to come back again. Every time we went was in the evening, the service was slow, it seemed like they were understaffed and it was clear all 3 times that we went that the baristas were totally miserable.  Tonight we got two different flavor frappucinos, which are essentially supposed to be sugar bombs, and neither was sweet. It took about 10 minutes for our 2 drinks to come out. The cashier was barely paying attention to us and didn't tell me my total or to pay, just listened to my order and looked off into the distance.  The place was also dirty, not the quality I usually expect at a Starbucks.  Like I said, this was the third time we went, so we really gave this place several chances to redeem itself and all 3 times the drinks just....weren't good! Why spend $7 on a coffee that you dont enjoy drinking? There's a Starbucks across the street at Kroger, maybe that one is better? We'll probably start looking for a small business coffee shop to frequent instead.
